<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="valuable-adj">valuable <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'væljuəbl/    美 /'væljuəbl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>值钱的；贵重的</strong></h4>
<p>worth a lot of money：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Her grandfather left her a valuable ring. 
她的祖父留给她一枚贵重的戒指。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>宝贵的；有价值的</strong></h4>
<p>very useful or important：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Although skills and talents bring great success, the most valuable thing one can hold is the heart.
尽管技能和天赋会带来极大的成功，但一个人所拥有的最宝贵的东西是心灵。</p><footer>2016 天津</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This gave him a valuable clue about the cause of the disease. 
这为他查明病因提供了一条很有价值的线索。</p><footer>人教⑤ – 1</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>invaluable /ɪn'væljuəbl/ adj   </p></div>